Notes on the monorepo layout

design-tokens is the canonical source. Use Style Dictionary to generate dist/tokens.css, dist/tokens.ts, dist/tokens.json. Publish to npm (e.g., @org/design-tokens) and use as dependency in other packages.

design-system (Stencil) consumes @org/design-tokens/dist/tokens.css in global/theme.css. Components never reference raw colors — only var(--ds-...).

lint-rules exports ESLint and stylelint rules; set these as devDependencies for consumer apps to enforce policy in PR CI.

tokens-validator is a small runtime/CI tool that checks theme overrides against the PUBLIC_TOKENS list.

example-apps prove cross-framework compatibility and are used in CI visual/a11y tests.

tools/contrast-checker runs the contrast matrix over all theme presets and is used in .github/workflows/validate-theme.yml.
